 Kim Hye Gyong, representative of the Democratic Workers�f Party, said that a peace-keeping mechanism should be established above anything else for peace and reunification on the Korean Peninsula. All the people should turn out in the struggle against the transfer and expansion of the U.S. military bases in south Korea and the U.S. forces' �gstrategic flexibility" and arms build-up, the speaker urged.
 Jong Kwang Hun, permanent representative of the People�fs Solidarity, stated that what the United States is mostly afraid of is independence and unity of the Korean nation rather than nukes and missiles. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Min Kyong U, former secretary general of the Reunification Solidarity, and Ri Tong Jin, former chairman of the Reunification Committee of the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils, who had been detained on the strength of the �gNational Security Law�h and were recently released, shouted slogan �gLet us achieve the reunification of the country by concerted efforts of the Korean nation.�h
 An art performance on the theme of national reunification was given by members of the children�fs reunification vanguard belonging to the �gGroup for Paektu-Halla Grand March for National Reunification�h. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
